parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in a crash
even though the vehicle was severely damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed or failed repair of recalled airbags can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Difficulty in scheduling recall repairs
lack of parts availability
and poor communication from dealerships and manufacturers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty airbag sensors can lead to false deployments or failure to deploy in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbag sensor light came on
and diagnosis revealed a faulty passenger seat airbag sensor mat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uncontrolled acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerated out of control
and the brakes were applied
but the vehicle continued to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ZKW headlight projector can cause the headlights to become dim or inoperable, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights are dim or do not illuminate
fog lights are brighter than headlights
headlight bulbs are burnt out
burning odor detected
reflector bowls are burnt or cracked
and reduced light output.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight wiring can cause the headlights to become inoperable, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights do not turn on
wiring insulation is brittle or crumbling
wires are exposed
and electrical tape is needed to wrap the wiring to avoid a potential fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear lighting can cause reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rear lights are inoperable
tail lights are intermittently off
and scorch marks are visible on the connectors and panels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden fire
smoke
or flames from the dashboard
headlights
or other electrical components; electrical system malfunctions
such as faulty wiring or short circuits.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can reduce visibility, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Headlights flickering or not working; dim or reduced light output; bare wires or broken wires in the headlight assembly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door locks can trap occupants inside the vehicle, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Doors cannot be unlocked from the inside or outside; central locking system malfunctions; inability to exit the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminated; airbag system malfunctions; failure to deploy airbags in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or fails to start; ignition system malfunctions.
